    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Be accessible from the start</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <p>Accessibility must never be an afterthought or a task to do once you've got <abbr title="Minimum Viable Product">MVP</abbr> out the door. You should be considering how you ensure services are accessible right from the start and throughout the design and delivery lifecycle.</p>
        <p>Designers creating user interactions and writing content, must consider who may be using the service, or may do in the future. If you know the service has a low number of disabled users than the national average, this may change in future, don't just design for now.</p>
        <p>Allowing our users to use services which are not accessible, makes the service harder to use, wastes time and money fixing problems in the future, and exposes us to unnecessary risk.</p>
    </div>
