<div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-full">
  <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Design for less</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
<p>Overloading a page with UI elements such as buttons, unnecessary links, cards, graphical elements, can make it overwhelming and cause cognitive overload. Make best use of whitespace to make things easier to understand, navigate and use. </p>
<p>Some things in design are functional, others purely aesthetic. If they aren't adding to the overall experience, then remove it - reduce the design to the necessary features for the user to complete their task.</p>
<p>When writing content, write only what you need to. Make the main thing on a page, the most important thing the user needs to do or understand.</p>
    </div>
