  <h2 class="govuk-heading-l">Design with context</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
<p>You should be designing service interactions, touchpoints and content based on knowlege of how and where the users of the service will use them. This is a key principle, applied through <a href="https://apply-the-service-standard.education.gov.uk/service-standard/1-understand-user-needs.html" target="_blank"> Service Standard at Point 1 - Understand users and their needs</a> </p>
<p>Understanding users' circumstances, culture, language, abilities and capabilities, helps us to design services and content that works for everyone.</p>
<p>This doesn't only enable us to design inclusive services, it also enables us to mitigate biases we may design into our service unintentionally.</p>
<p>Provide information and functionality in context - at the point the user is most likely to need it. Save the user from having to hunt for it, or missing it altogether.</p>
    </div>
